            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I was wondering whether this fairly old ticket is still relevant, but seeing the references in https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/6129 makes me think that it still solves a user issue.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if we'd need version specific modules here, at least major+minor, to allow different user packages to depend on Cython 3.2 and Cython 3.5 independently at the same time. If we can't provide that, we'd have to be *very* conservative regarding changes in the public runtime package. We already have that today, really, but not a lot packages depend on Cython at runtime yet. That might change in the future.",
