        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> The \"version specific\" problem is a big complication\r\n\r\nWhat is a big complication. Is it a problem to release with Cython also Shadow file in separate package? I think even publishing it with every sub-minor version should not be a problem. The user will just pin cython as build dependency and shaddow as a runtime dependency with the same version. Or am I missing something?\r\n\r\n> I'm fairly sure it's a real problem, but less sure that this is the right solution.\r\n\r\nIs there any other possible solution? Pure python mode, if intended to be run without compilation, needs to have imported cython module as dependency. Dependency in form of whole cython is too heavy. It is possible that shadow file will be copied directly to the source code of project but in this case we need to have #6129 fixed.\r\n ",
