            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> What is a big complication.\r\n\r\nThe complication is that for runtime dependencies we have to assume there will be multiple packages depending on different versions of Cython_Shadow. So it needs to be kept fairly strictly backwards compatible. (Which is different than for build, where it's usually done in an isolated environment and can use an exact version)\r\n\r\n> It is possible that shadow file will be copied directly to the source code of project but in this case we need to have https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/6129 fixed.\r\n\r\nThat does seem like the only other option to me. if we did that I think it would be better to have a directive to control \"this is what should be considered the Cython module\" rather than trace imports though.",
