        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> So it needs to be kept fairly strictly backwards compatible.\r\n\r\nJust several thoughts:\r\n1. Cython_Shadow should follow common compatibility as any other library so I think is nothing unusual. We can still deprecate API etc. and users should be able to pin the version anyway\r\n2. In Cython we must already keep strict backward compatibility. I think in Cython 3.0 broke the world because of the backward incompatible changes (planned, communicated, documented but still it happened)\r\n\r\n> That does seem like the only other option to me.\r\n\r\nI agree. Honestly, I don't know what is better. Both have pros and cons.",
